title: FAA: Lasers target two planes over Boston
text:
FAA: Lasers target two planes over Boston Adv: 
Jul 23, 2015 Adv: 
BOSTON, MA - US Federal Aviation Administration officials said that flight crews of two Boston-bound planes reported lasers pointed at their aircraft over Boston on Wednesday evening. 
Air Canada flight reACA368 was approximately two miles from Boston airport when its crew reported seeing the lasers at about 10:39pm. An hour later, the crew of JetBlue flight number 418 reported seeing the lasers, also about two miles from the airport.
